> 1. The web browser to `https://github.com/login/oauth/authorize?...` opens;
> 2. The web server starts at `localhost:<port>` (port is random each time);
> 3. The OAuth flow redirects back to localhost with `?code=...`;
> 3. The local server shuts down;
> 4. We exchange `code` for `access_token` by POSTing to `https://github.com/login/oauth/access_token`.
> 
> You can verify that the authorization token you've just obtained works:
> ```sh
> curl https://<TOKEN>@api.github.com/user
> ```
> 
> TODO:
> - [x] Detect currently available port number;
> - [x] Generate random unguessable `state`;
> - [x] Verify `state` upon request to localhost;
> - [x] Repackage this from "main" to something usable;
> - [x] ~Figure out where to securely store the token~ It is in `~/.config/gh` for now.

